Crooked Oak Family:

We know this is a stressful time for all of you. It is for us as well.

There is some misinformation being spread by some disgruntled, former employees that is not only untrue, but frankly, shows that they don't truly have our students' best interests in mind. If you would like accurate facts regarding the district's positive COVID tests or need information on virtual learning, please feel free to contact your child's school directly. We would be glad to inform you of everything we can.

We're all in this together and will get through it that way.

post_text:
What a First Day of School! We have to send a big SHOUT-OUT to all of the families, parents, students, teachers, administrators, paras, basically everyone who came to campus today for an amazingly smooth first day back. There were tons of masks being worn, there was social distancing in every classroom, and even navigating campus with all of the construction going on was fairly smooth. The day was not without it's hiccups, but those are to be expected when we're all swimming in uncharted waters. It was a great day all around!

We would like to make all parents aware of the morning drop off locations so we can continue to provide the safest possible environment for our students. Please take a look at the map and make sure and follow the arrows according to the school your student belongs to when dropping off in the morning.

Thank you for your flexibility, understanding, and patience as we continue this unusual school year.

Crooked Oak Band
August 11 at 12:12 PM ·

Big news! I would like to take a moment to introduce myself. I am Mr. Johns, the new Band Director at Crooked Oak! I just graduated from the University of Oklahoma with a degree in Music Education. I was in many different ensembles during my time there, including the Pride of Oklahoma Marching Band, Symphony Band, Trombone Choir, and the Jazz Bands. This is my first year teaching and I am very excited to get started with everyone on the 19th! I have done a lot of stuff to get the band room ready for school the past few days, and I still have a lot to do! If anyone has any questions at all please feel free to shoot me an email at zjohns@crookedoak.org

shared_text:
Crooked Oak High School
July 28 at 8:48 PM ·

This post is coming from Ms Knight. Any questions or concerns, please feel free to message me!

The school has been busy buying lots of cleaning supplies for the classroom. Unfortunately, a lot of places have a quantity limit. This year, instead of putting out a supply list, we are putting out a wish list. If your student is coming to in-person school this year (or if you’d just like to help), please send as many of the items from the list as you feel comfortable donating. Thank you for your help!

1. Disinfectant wipes (Clorox wipes or other brands)
2. Hand sanitizer
3. Disinfectant spray (Lysol or other brands)
4. Bottle of hydrogen peroxide (mixed with water, it can be used as a disinfectant)
5. Box of Kleenex

We appreciate everything you as parents do to support us! We are looking forward to this coming school year!

shared_text:
Crooked Oak High School
June 16 at 6:37 PM ·

Graduation: Friday, June 19, 2020
7:30 pm at CO Football Field
2201 SE 22nd
OKC, OK, 73129

We will be attempting to stream the entire ceremony on FB live. Please have anyone interested in watching, like our FB page before hand.
We ask for patience with this as it will be our first time to attempt a live stream.
We will also be videoing the entire program. If the live stream does not work, we will be posting the program in its entirety to this page on Saturday.

Due to shortage of parking, please bring as few cars as possible per family.

Both bleachers will be open, along with chairs on the field. Please keep a social distance of 6-ft apart from those not in your family.

In order for all to be able to see, no balloons will be allowed. Please leave all balloons in the car.

Finally, but most importantly, this is a formal ceremony. Please be considerate of any and all speakers. This includes but is not limited to not speaking and walking around while they are speaking.

We look forward to seeing everyone on Friday!!!

Central Oak Elementary
May 27 at 8:10 PM ·

We are so excited to announce that beginning Monday and for the next two weeks we are going to do an in person summer school. We will have the students come in for summer school Monday-Wednesday-Friday from 9-12:30. We will continue the Tuesday-Thursday play at the park at all lunch sites. Lunch will continue to be delivered each day. We will be taking the opportunity on Tuesday-Thursday to deep clean the spaces we use in summer school. As we navigate the current situation, at this time we will not be running buses. Therefore, all in- person summer school will be parent drop-off and pick-up only. Breakfast will begin at 8:45. Lunch will be served from 12-12:30.
If you are already enrolled just show up on Monday. If not you can go to the STREAM website and enroll. If you can’t find that we can get you enrolled Monday morning.

https://sites.google.com/crookedoak.org/costream/home

Crooked Oak Ruf-Nex Athletics
May 22 at 7:09 PM ·

COVID 19 Crooked Oak Athletics

The health and safety of our student/athletes is our biggest concern. The following guidelines will be followed by coaches and athletes.

Athletes will receive a temperature scan prior to workouts.
There will be no use of locker rooms until further notice.
Athletes will be provided a face mask.
When being transported by school vehicle coaches and athletes must wear face mask.
Summer football workouts will be divided into smaller groups to ensure social distancing.
All coaches will wipe down equipment between workouts.
Athletes will be required to practice good hygiene routines. Athletes will wash hands prior to and following workouts.
The following guidelines can be added to at any time to ensure the health and safety of our athletes.

Crooked Oak Afjrotc
May 1 at 3:30 PM ·

2020 SENIOR SHOUT OUT
Caet Jahre White was a part of our corps for two and a half years. During his time with us he was a member of the Drill Team, Marksmanship Team, and our Kitty Hawk Air Society for a year each. He spent his senior year as Charlie Flight's Deputy Commander.
His favorite memory from AFJROTC is just being a part of the corps.
After high school he plans to complete basic training and begin his career in the U.S. Navy.
His advice to underclassmen is: "Enjoy high school while you have time because when it’s over it’s over!"
Thank you for your time with us Jahre, and the best of luck to you next year!

Crooked Oak Afjrotc
May 1 at 3:26 PM ·

2020 SENIOR SHOUT OUT
Cadet Cristal Sustaita was a part of our corps for four year. During her time with us she acted as our Drill Team Commander for a year. She was also a member of our Drill Team for two years and a Kitty Hawk Air Society member for one year.
Her favorite memory from AFJROTC is the Change of Command Ceremony, where she was able to pass her staff rope to the new Drill Team Commander.
After high school she plans to attend OSU and pursue a degree in Allied Health.
Her advice to underclassmen is:" Get involved, in everything! whether it’s drill, clubs, sports etc. High school goes by in the blink of an eye, in the end you only regret the chances you didn’t take!"
Thank you for your time with us Cristal, and the best of luck to you next year!

Crooked Oak Afjrotc
May 1 at 3:06 PM ·

2020 SENIOR SHOUT OUT
Cadet Jennifer Ortega was a part of our corps for four years. During her time with us she acted as our Vice Corps Commander for a year. She was also a member of our Drill and Color Guard teams for two years, and a Kitty Hawk Air Society member for three years.
Her favorite memory from AFJROTC is trips, camps, weekend activities, PT, and even just hanging out in the classroom.
After high school she plans to attend OSU and major in Biology to pursue a career in optometry.
Her advice to underclassmen is: "Always be involved! Go to all the community service activites provided and join any squadrons that might interest you! Being involved in these things will come in handy when you're applying for scholarships and colleges! Also value and cherish your time in the program because time will go by quick! I already miss it ):"
Thank you for your time with us Jennifer, best of luck to you next year!

Good Friday morning Central Oak family. I hope everyone is doing well. As we approach the last week of our distance learning plan, we would like to say thank you for all of your hard work.
We still have about 300 students that have not come in to pick up their supplies. We are going to have the remaining materials set up outside Tuesday and Wednesday for drive up pick up from 10-1 with no appointment necessary. If you pick up during those times we will have a special treat for you. Additionally, if you bring in your library books, we will have something special for you.
Have a great weekend and thanks for your help. 📚✂️✏️🖍

Her favorite memory from AFJROTC is being named top cadet in the state of Oklahoma.
After high school, she plans to head off to basic training to start her career in the U.S Air Force.
Her advice to underclassmen is: "Get involved because if you don’t, you won’t have fun in JROTC!"
Thank you for your time with us Daisy, best of luck to you next year!

shared_text:
Crooked Oak High School
April 7 at 3:36 PM ·

We have had a few questions. I did an online meeting with seniors, but I wanted to clarify here.

There WILL be a graduation ceremony. We just do not know when. As soon as it is ok for people to gather in bigger groups again, we will start planning. When we have a date, we will let everyone know.

Seniors will get everything they paid for with their senior fees. All seniors will receive a yearbook, a cap and gown, and a T-shirt. When these things come in, we will set up schedules to come and pick them up. The caps and gowns should be scheduled by next week so that you will have them.

We will have a senior activity. I will be doing another zoom call in the near future to decide what exactly that will be. However, date will depend on when we are allowed to gather in groups larger than 10.

As always, if you have any questions, please feel free to message me on here or through email at LKnight@crookedoak.org

-Ms Knight

Seniors will get everything they paid for with their senior fees. All seniors will receive a yearbook, a cap and gown, and a T-shirt. When these things come in, we will set up schedules to come and pick them up. The caps and gowns should be scheduled by next week so that you will have them.

We will have a senior activity. I will be doing another zoom call in the near future to decide what exactly that will be. However, date will depend on when we are allowed to gather in groups larger than 10.

As always, if you have any questions, please feel free to message me on here or through email at LKnight@crookedoak.org

-Ms Knight

Hello! I hope everyone is safe and well during this crazy time!

Every student has been added to my Google Classroom, so all you will need to do is log in to your classroom app and accept my request.
Online enrichment activities will be added weekly for students to complete online! The first activity will be uploaded no later than this Friday at 3pm.
Paper copies will be available at the middle and high school offices for students without access to a computer and/or internet.
There will also be some supplemental music activities and opportunities uploaded often onto my Google Classrooms to keep you busy!

shared_text:
Oklahoma State Department of Education
March 26 at 3:22 PM ·

Exciting news! 🎉 We have partnered with OETA to provide in-home learning opportunities for students. The goal is to bring parents, students and teachers together with content and curriculum to meet educational needs while schools are closed due to coronavirus.

Beginning Monday, March 30, OETA will be adjusting its daytime schedule to provide curriculum-based programming for students over the air on its broadcast channel, OETA WORLD. Programs will include PBS favorites like NOVA, Nature, American Experience and PBS KIDS programming.

Programming changes to OETA WORLD will take place Monday through Friday from 6 a.m. until 6 p.m. until the end of the school year.

Teachers and parents are encouraged to visit OETA.tv/LearningAtHome to view an updated program schedule, OETA’s statewide channel list, curriculum and activities.

shared_text:
Crooked Oak High School
March 23 at 4:20 PM ·

I have had lots of questions regarding State Superintendent Joy Hofemister’s announcement. From what I’ve read, she will be recommending to the State Board of Education on WEDNESDAY, to close all school buildings for the remainder of the year. Her plan will include some type of “distance learning”.

First, none of this will be official until after the board meeting on Wednesday morning. The board will have to vote to approve her recommendation for this to take effect.

Second, what will distance learning look like? We do not know. I am sure that the state department will provide us guidance if this is approved. When that happens and we have a plan, we will let all students and parents know.

Finally, please know that we care about each and every one of you! We will continue to provide information as we learn. Don’t forget, we will be at the 4 designated spots handing out lunch every day this week. If that schedule ever changes, we will let you know!

Stay safe and stay healthy!!

post_text: Please read this message from our high school personal principal regarding last night's events at the basketball playoff game.
shared_text:
Laura Knight
February 22 at 12:27 AM ·

First, I am very proud of our girls and boys for taking home the W and becoming district camps!!!!

Second, this is for all of those that have seen the video. I heard it in person. It was shocking. The mama bear was coming out in me! I love these kids with my whole heart. But I say this often and will say it here. Always give the appropriate people a chance to handle things. Their administration removed him, replaced him with a person that went to lengths to ensure that everything else was announced correctly. Their administration sought out ours to apologize. Their fans, administration, and coaches treated us well. I know that does not take away the hurt, but please know that they took care of it, it was not ignored.

I CANNOT SAY THIS NEXT PART ENOUGH: Those girls handled it beautifully and rose above! Please, please do not let social media bring us down, we are better than that.

Dear Families:
On Thursday, November 21, 2019, from 5:00 p.m. – 8:00 p.m., come enjoy a terrific dinner at S&B’s Burger Joint in support of the Crooked Oak Special Education Department. All you have to do is put your receipt in the designated collection bucket before you leave the restaurant, and we will receive 20% of your receipt amount. This money will help provide student incentives and other benefits for our program.
Thank you for supporting us! We appreciate you and all that you do.

Address: S&B’s Burger Joint
1909 S. Douglas Blvd.
Midwest City, OK 73130

Crooked Oak's AFJROTC Corps and Band will be participating in a Donation Drive to help the City Rescue Mission of Downtown OKC. Here is a list of all donations that we will be accepting (plus non-perishable food items and childrens toys for Christmas).
The Donation Drive will be taking place from November 18 - December 18. We encourage families and friends to get together with your cadets and donate to maximize the amount of donations we're able to provide to this organization.
For flights, tote boxes will be set up in the Rec Room, find the one with your flight name and place your items there.
Crooked Oak Public Schools Crooked Oak High School Crooked Oak Band

post_text: Crooked Oak Schools has a rich legacy and tradition that can be attributed to generations of outstanding alumni. Crooked Oak alumni range from titans of industry to professional athletes and each one would tell you their success was influenced by a great teacher or coach. Coach Leo Thurman is one such example. Please help us and his son Randy, in honoring Coach Thurman by donating to our Field House Remodel project.

We would like to congratulate all of our soccer teams for a great season!!!
This morning, our COE GREY and COE WHITE teams went head to head for the Championship!!! It was a spectacular game with a never quit attitude from everyone! Grey team came out on top with a 4-2 win!
Once again, COE dominates the Destiny Soccer League with 1st, 2nd, 3rd and 5th places regular season while making it a 1st and 2nd place finish in the tournament!!!
Thank you to all of our families, friends and fans for supporting our teams!!! ⚽️🏆💫

This is a very prestigious honor and we are thrilled to be so well represented.
